media.alt_text:
Panel 1: Shen is gesturing with his hand and happily saying "I love it when girls try to be scary."

Panel 2: Shen puts his hands forward in 'claw' position, big yellow and red glints in his eyes and the top half of his face cloaked in purple shadow. The background is squiggly indigo lines on a purple background emanating from his head. He says "They just go RAAAH~. And it's more cute than scary"

Panel 3: Shen turns around, looking at a girl with cocentric circle pupils, sharp teeth, an x shaped scar on the right side of her face and a band-aid on the left, and messy blonde hair in a ponytail. She is wearing a white tank-top and black pants. This it the Professional Hater, who has shown up in the comics previously. He says "Hey, try to be scary for me."

Panel 4: Side view as she hands a happy Shen a piece of paper with something written on it.

Panel 5: Shen's expression sours into a something more somber and concerned as he says "this is my home address".

Comic titled "How I Imagine Chess Pieces Move"

Panel 1: Titled "Pawn". A humanized white pawn on a chess board, his helmet crowned with a metal ball, runs forward swinging his sword a bit. 

Panel 2: Titled "Knight". A dark purple horse with a blue mane leaps happily from one white spot on the chess board to a black spot.

Panel 3: Titled "Bishop". A humanized black bishop on a chess board is down on one knee, aiming a sniper rifle along the diagonal. A closeup of the muzzle of the sniper rifled reveals that he himself, the bishop, is also loaded into it as a bullet.

Panel 4: Titled "Roo (too shakily written, crossed out) Roo (too shakily written again, crossed out) BRO FUCK (shakily written)". A stone tower cuts along a straight line through the board, shaking the whole board (and in fact, the whole panel) in the process and carving out a deep hole. There are bits of the board flying everywhere. The tower has a tiny content face on it as it causes this destruction.

media.alt_text:
Panel 1: Shen is happily running, grasping the string of a bright yellow balloon. The balloon is labeled "Self Esteem".

Panel 2: Life steps into the panel holding a needle to the balloon. Shen skids to a halt in front of Life but it's too late -- the needle has popped the balloon, it's shape still vaguely outlined in the air by the chunks of yellow rubber now falling apart.

Panel 3: Yellow balloon chunks rain down, a few landing on Shen's messy hair. He is distraught. He says: "Why"

Panel 4: Shen is surprised to find Life, backlit by the bright sun, now holding out a way BIGGER yellow balloon labeled "Self Esteem" towards him, offering it to him.
